  "introduced_in": "APU-3LS-01",
  "last_updated_in": "EVL-RT-05",
  "notes": "APU-3LS-01 policy (last updated by EVL-RT-05). APU is observation-only and emits PR-update readiness observations. Canonical authority remains with AEX (admission), PQX (execution closure), EVL (eval evidence), TPA (policy/scope), CDE (continuation/closure), SEL (final gate signal), LIN (lineage), REP (replay), and GOV per docs/architecture/system_registry.md. APU consumes core_loop_pre_pr_gate_result (CLP), agent_core_loop_run_record (AGL), agent_pr_ready_result (CLP-02 guard), prl_gate_result (PRL), and pr_test_shard_first_readiness_observation (EVL) as readiness inputs and emits an agent_pr_update_ready_result evidence artifact. APU enforces the artifact-backed evidence invariant: 'no artifact = it did not happen'. Claimed 3LS usage without artifact refs is invalid. PR body prose, comments, and CI success cannot substitute for artifact_refs. F3L-01 wires PRL failure-normalization evidence into APU so a CLP-blocked repo-mutating slice cannot be observed as PR-update ready until PRL evidence (gate result, failure packet refs, repair/eval candidate refs as applicable) is present. F3L-02 closes the manual seam between CLP gate detection and PRL by auto-invoking scripts/run_pre_pr_reliability_gate.py from the APU runner whenever CLP reports the blocking gate status on a repo-mutating slice with missing or stale PRL evidence; the invocation record is recorded as an observation on the readiness artifact. F3L-03 makes PRL artifact persistence deterministic by writing prl_gate_result.json plus per-artifact subdirectories (failure_packets/, repair_candidates/, eval_candidates/) under outputs/prl/, so APU and replay consumers ingest file-based evidence rather than parsing stdout NDJSON. EVL-RT-05 wires shard-first readiness evidence into APU so a repo-mutating slice cannot be observed as PR-update ready unless the shard-first readiness observation (or, when not supplied directly, the evl_shard_first_evidence block recorded by CLP) is present and consistent. APU surfaces shard_first_status, shard_first_evidence_status, shard_first_reason_codes, shard_first_fallback_used, shard_first_full_suite_detected, and shard_first_fallback_reason_codes on the agent_pr_update_ready_result. APU does not run pytest, recompute selection, or rebuild the observation. EVL retains all selection, shard mapping, and shard-execution authority. PRL retains all classification, repair-candidate, and eval-candidate authority. AEX/PQX/CDE/SEL retain canonical signal authority and consume APU output as a readiness input only."
}
